 ready (and if i=\r\nt is needed), a guru may come and take one&#39;s sadhana to the next level.\n&gt; &gt;=\r\n  \n&gt; &gt; (2) A guru can mould the correct attitude in sadhaka before a sadhan=\r\na is taken up.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; However, there are sadhakas initiated in powerful =\r\nmantras and not having the right attitude. For example, I know people initi=\r\nated into Bagalamukhi mantra and trying to use it to win litigation. If one=\r\n does not know that a &quot;Mahavidya&quot; (supreme knowledge) is for overcoming con=\r\nditioning and realizing self and not for winning court cases, one&#39;s initiat=\r\nion is no good.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; On the other hand, I know some people not formall=\r\ny initiated into Chandipath, but doing Chandi homam daily with saptashati a=\r\nnd also navarna mantra. I know that they do not have any specific material =\r\ngoals and are overcoming the few desires that were originally there at the =\r\nback of the mind. The are making quick progress spiritually and their think=\r\ning is getting transformed nicely. Despite having no formal initiation, are=\r\nn&#39;t they worshipping Chandi as a Mahavidya?\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; Bottomline is that on=\r\ne can mould one&#39;s own attitude through a formal initiation or through readi=\r\nng scriptures, satsanga and constant contemplation. One thing may work bett=\r\ner in one case and another thing in another case.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; (3) A guru can =\r\nteach the correct procedure of a sadhana.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; However, role of proced=\r\nural correctness in success is a higher in sadhanas for specific results th=\r\nan sadhana for spiritual progress. I maintain that the art of getting speci=\r\nfic results from sadhanas is being hidden more and more as Kali progresses,=\r\n for a reason. I suggest that it is useless to even think in those terms an=\r\nd pursue it.\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; Mantras like navarna mantra can just be meditated on=\r\n, without any s