pecialities that need initiation, as i=\r\nn the case of Mahavidyas such as Kali or Sri.\n&gt; &gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; &gt; 5.\tVishnusahasr=\r\nanama, Sivasahasranama, Aditya hrdayam etc do not need initiation as they f=\r\nall under stotra category only. Lalitasahasranama and Devi Mahatmyam are tr=\r\naditionally viewed not MERELY as stotras or parts of puranas. They have a l=\r\narger status as integral parts of a Mahavidya sadhana. Chanting them withou=\r\nt initiation is not recommended especially when the reader combines the nav=\r\narna or shodashi mantras too as an integral part of the chanting.\n&gt; &gt; &gt;    =\r\n        \n&gt; &gt; &gt; 6.\tI know from personal interaction that acharyas belonging =\r\nto both Kanchi as well as Sringeri paramparas recommend initiation for both=\r\n the sadhanas of Sri Sri Chandi and Sri Vidya along with their respective N=\r\nAVAKSHARI AND SHODASAKSHARI mantras which are treated as an INTEGRAL LIMB (=\r\nANGA) of the sadhana. Acharyas of both these traditions hold that one needs=\r\n to be initiated to chant the Navarna as well as shodashakshari mantras.\n&gt; =\r\n&gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; &gt; 7.\tRecapping my earlier stance, Devi Mahatmyam is a great text =\r\nthat has an independent status by itself as part of a Mahavidya. It is simu=\r\nltaneously a Mahavidya, a Yogasastra as well as an Advaitic text in the spi=\r\nrit of the Upanishads. ***As a Mahavidya the Navakshari is an integral part=\r\n of Sri Sri Chandi path***. Thus tradition holds that one needs to be initi=\r\nated to chant it. However if one wishes to benefit from the Yoga-Vedanta or=\r\n Sacred myth aspects of the Devi Mahatmyam, , reading the sacred myth in th=\r\ne vernacular has been recommended in my write-up, as chanting the original =\r\nalong with the navakshari  amounts to practicing the sadhana of a Mahavidya=\r\n. In that case it is recommended to be initiated and go through the special=\r\nised sadhanas properly under guidance.\n&gt; &gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; &gt; 8.\tArguably if an unin=\r\nitiated person reads the Devi Mahatmyam in the original Sanskrit as part of=\r\n the *Pauranik* approach and not as a Mahavidya, it has an inherent problem=\r\n in our times.  The problem with attempting to do a parayana of Devi Mahatm=\r\nyam from texts alone (without initiation) is that most readers inadvertentl=\r\ny end up also chanting the Navarna mantra or stotras such as the Siddhakunj=\r\nika stotram which too contain the bijaksharas.\n&gt; &gt; &gt;  \n&gt; &gt; &gt; 9.\tI you caref=\r\nully peruse my write-up on the Devi Mahatmyam, forget translating, nowhere =\r\ndo I put down the Navarna mantra even in writing. Neither have I attempted =\r\nto write a commentary on it. Translations of mantras do not have the power =\r\nof the original mantra as Sabda or Vak. However it is recommended to know t=\r\nhe essence or import (artha) of the mantra and its sadhana while chanting i=\r\nt. Infact `artha&#39; is the import, the essence of `Vak&#39;, not a translation! \n=\r\n&gt; &gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; 10.\tFor those who are already doing Sri Sri Chandi path withou=\r\nt initiation, there is no need to worry or be confused. There has to be a c=\r\nertain level of samskara to be attracted to Sri Sri Chandi path itself. We =\r\nall have it. Otherwise we would not be doing it (initiation or no initiatio=\r\nn). Please keep doing whatever you are doing. Just be cautious not to do sa=\r\nkama sadhana. As Narasimha garu has rightly pointed out it is better to jus=\r\nt do the sadhana WITHOUT asking for any favours or results. That attitude i=\r\ntself will reduce a lot of the potential problem. Things will happen on the=\r\nir own accord in the natural flow. Leave the rest to the compassionate Godd=\r\ness.              \n&gt; &gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; Hope the above pointers help in clearing an=\r\ny confusion.  \n&gt; &gt; &gt; \n&gt; &gt; &gt; Regards,\n&gt; &gt; &gt; Satya Prakash                \n&gt; =\r\n&gt; &gt;